review_blob: Bottle to glass. Pours a hazy gold without much head. Aroma is light and sweet, as is the pallet. Taste is sweet but finishes slightly bitter with a tiny is aftertaste. Still pretty good.

Bottle to glass. Pours a hazy slightly orange gold. Minimal head, nothing special to look at. Aroma is excellent, smells like a pumpkin pie. Great feel, sweet flavor with all the taste of a pie down to the crust. Well balanced finish. For a specialty seasonal, pretty great dessert type beer. 8.6 ABV.
Bottle to cup. Pours a hazy gold amber. Minimal head. Palate is pleasantly thick. Taste is malty and sweet. Slightly bitter finish but not as hoppy as expected.

Can to cup. Clear gold, minimal head. Aroma is hoppy but a bit too floral. Palate is unremarkable. Palate is busy with a slight hop finish, some mild slice notes, then sweetness. Not bad, especially for gluten free, but not spectacular.

Bottle to glass. Pours a very dark brown with minimal head. Aroma is very malty, with hints of raisin. Mouth is very smooth and moderately thick. Taste is sweet, malty, and very well balanced. A great brown.

Can to glass. Pours an opaque black with tan head and fine lacing. Aroma is mild, with roast and chocolate coming to the front. Mouth is medium, thinner than expected but not bad. Flavor is complex, with coffee and burnt sugar notes as well as the aroma flavors. Finishes slightly sweet / tart. Pretty good porter.

Can to glass. Pours a clear copper. Light head with fine lacing. Aroma is citrusy hop and some sweet caramel. Medium thick mouth. Sweet malt flavor with good hop finish. Maltier than expected from an IPA but smooth and tasty. 7.5 ABV
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle at home in IPA glass. Pours very clear, light copper. Aroma is hoppy but not overly strong. Medium mouth feel and not a ton of flavor. Decent balance with a bit of a hop finish. OK but not spectacular.

Pours nearly black with some light through the edges. Minimal head and lacing. Aroma is pumpkin pie and spices. Mouth is medium, thinner than expected. Taste is amazing. Great pumpkin flavor and spices, excellent finish worth some toasted finish. Well balanced. 8.6% ABV.

Pours a orange gold, fairly clear, with a good amount of head. Coarse lacing. Hoppy aroma with citrus notes. Moderately thick feel. Good malt balance but flavor is very hop centered, as it should be. Notes of the jasmine tea is infused with, but hard for me to pick out as Im not a huge tea drinker. Finish is very hoppy and stays with you for a while.
beer_name: Milwaukee Brewing Hop Freak Double IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a dark red brown with light had and minimal lacing. Aroma is nice and sour, with hints of sweetness. Palate is moderate, thinner than I expected. Taste is immediately sour and intense with a crisp, sweetly sour finish. 7% ABV. Really good sour ale.

Pours a hazy gold without much head. Aroma is floral and grassy, not as hoppy so expected. Palate is medium thin. Taste is citrusy and sweet without much hop presence really. 8.5%, Rhinelander Brewing Co.

Pours a deep, hazy, dark brown amber with light just making it through the edges. Nice light beige head and lots of fine lacing. Aroma is mild with toffee notes. Palate is full and smooth, great feel. Taste is delicious; caramel, toffee, burnt sugar, and finally raisins or some fruity flavor I cant quite pin down. Excellent beer.
